[SN]TITLE[SN]
Swansea partygoer Jordan Miers' inquest opened

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An inquest into the death of a man whose body was found in Swansea marina weeks after he went missing after a night out has been opened and adjourned.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Jordan Miers, 21, was reported missing in Swansea on 19 December.
Extensive searches of the area involving divers were carried out and his body was discovered on 8 January.
The hearing was held at Swansea Civic Centre by Swansea and Neath Port Talbot Coroner Colin Phillips.
